<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4487] gettimeofday: windows implementation not quoting source, applying license to foreign code</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4487</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/lib/cpp/src/thrift/windows/GetTimeOfDay.cpp&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/lib/cpp/src/thrift/windows/GetTimeOfDay.cpp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;uses Code that is at least from March 2007;&#160;unless the original author of GetTimeOfDay.cpp is the same who submitted the code to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.openasthra.com/wp-content/uploads/gettimeofday.c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.openasthra.com/wp-content/uploads/gettimeofday.c&lt;/a&gt;&#160;(link dead, web archive link:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://web.archive.org/web/20070328134250/http://www.openasthra.com/wp-content/uploads/gettimeofday.c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://web.archive.org/web/20070328134250/http://www.openasthra.com/wp-content/uploads/gettimeofday.c&lt;/a&gt;&#160;), very likely isn&apos;t code that can be assigned to the Apache foundation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t really tell when this file has been added.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
