                            <comment id="16740860" author="jking3" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2019 22:59:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s an alternate implementation here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10905892/equivalent-of-gettimeday-for-windows&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10905892/equivalent-of-gettimeday-for-windows&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t find any copyright information on the original, and I can&apos;t see the file history where it originally was added to the project, which means it probably came in a very long time ago...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16741269" author="marcusmuellerkit" created="Sat, 12 Jan 2019 12:31:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m sorry, but you&apos;ve changed the issue type from &quot;Bug&quot; to &quot;Question&quot;, and I had to change that back.&lt;br/&gt;
There&apos;s no question in here. To make this clear: This is code that clearly doesn&apos;t belong to Apache, and that clearly wasn&apos;t licensed by the original author under the license that it is now being distributed under.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a breach of license and leaves open many question. Re-licensing someone else&apos;s code isn&apos;t a &quot;Question&quot;, it&apos;s a code bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16741325" author="jensg" created="Sat, 12 Jan 2019 15:44:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Your report also leaves a number of open questions, as it consists of a good portion of guesswork. We understand the issue, but &quot;unless&quot; and &quot;very likely&quot; and &quot;can&apos;t really tell&quot; is not really solid ground to build upon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16742035" author="jking3" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2019 12:57:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am replacing it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
